
Overview of verb tighten

The verb tighten has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (8) tighten, fasten -- (make tight or tighter; "Tighten the wire")
2. (1) tighten -- (become tight or tighter; "The rope tightened")
3. (1) stiffen, tighten, tighten up, constrain -- (restrict; "Tighten the rules"; "stiffen the regulations")
4. reduce, tighten -- (narrow or limit; "reduce the influx of foreigners")
